mij last to you was on the 31th ppast, sence recd yod. of 20 ditto, as for Cas. abshall I hope to
know the needfull I ginst, to accomodate yd & my freind m. Ednd warner you have prevailed
ommee for £100- realy such accomodarons do nott blease mee att all, & I can nott thanck you
for that, butt vere much blame, for itt is a jeare ago, that you would not trouble mee
in that finde, nay of the last £200- never no more, & now againe £100- & has £100-
more before this comeste yo handes, you need nott to Jugure what a goung man makes
so werrj of to good old freinds corrispendency for I see opently that you can not be saved affer
that rate butt rather loost, by our trade, which never in this wold was so poore as noww, &
the last sergible Jmnondarons will bring itt so low that if the least frenck bout comes
so sts any thing, itt will loose itts breath, there by is no mony to be reeaved, & yett m.
collien is not pleased to considder any of our miserable conditions wee are under
Inclosed you have the needfull accctt. there is resting in all 11 spanish cloathes & due
you I ballance £707„18„4 which finding right please to note accordinglly. I now mele
you debtor for the deets sransported mee for yd acctt. by the wedw boels for I finde no hopee
to recoven any thing, which if I do shall come in yd creditt. I have also made you
dibtor for £14„4„4 att 35„6 for the spanish cloth for my accctt. which hope is to content
I finde in standing out debes for yor acctt about £1100:- flemish amonght, which the wed.
amustens for a cloth sold 12 marck ƒ132.12- & hath made for an aggreement of about 32
that is the first bad dibt I had yett though itt be much more then for you the
pueatest cause of herbreakeing is the mundation, for her mother is dead semetime a go and
lest a good parceel of landes, which now hare lost, & should have been sould, which had
butther well anough in a condition to pay every one, & to continew her trade now god keep
iun from worses for itt is avine, that wee do not knw whow to trust, & yett wee have no
sall att all, & had not this 2 morths: if I may advise you, draw no more upon mee, for st
you please not to take notice of yo owne Intrest & respect, I must not do itt whilst I returne
you thanckes for yd kinde presentatior . Please to observe that yd bill of 20 Jan. is upon
